info","should_display_ad_info":false},"serialized_frtp_identifiers":null,"debug_info":null,"inform_treatment_for_community_notes":null,"message":{"text":"Escape the rain and immerse your family in the magical world of children\u2019s book illustration at our latest exhibition, Childhood Classics. This collection brings together timeless artworks, from early 20th-century pen and ink drawings by Sarah Noble Ives to modern digital masterpieces by Mo Willems. Delight in original pieces from iconic artists like Dr. Seuss, Maurice Sendak, and Garth Williams, and rediscover beloved characters such as Babar, Eloise, and The Cat in the Hat. Curated from the collection of Lois Sarkisian and Lee Cohen, co-founders of Every Picture Tells A Story, this exhibition offers a rich historical perspective on the evolution of children\u2019s literature. Perfect for a rainy day, this indoor activity invites families to embark on a whimsical journey through the history of storytelling and illustration, sparking imagination and nostalgia for all ages! Admission is free for children!
